==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: infighting
<hw>infighting</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>in-</ets> +
<ets>fighting</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>contention among members of
the same organization (usually concealed from outsiders), sometimes of a
bitter, intense, or prolonged character.</def> <note>[Such
<ex>infighting</ex> may lead to
<hascons><er>factionalism</er></hascons>.]</note>
<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>fighting, such as boxing, at close
quarters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>rough-and-tumble, free-for-all fighting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infile</ent>⟦br⟧
